There are 2 problemes with the HighlightReconciler:

 * if you select a symbol the first time the HighlightReconciler#updateAnnotations is called on time if you select second time a symbol the HighlightReconciler#updateAnnotations is called twice etc

It's because the call of collectHighlights add every time a listener to a job:

---------------------------------------
finder.addJobChangeListener(new JobChangeAdapter() {
	@Override
	public void done(IJobChangeEvent event) {
		if (event.getResult() == Status.OK_STATUS) {
			updateAnnotations(finder.getHighlights())
		}
	}
})
---------------------------------------

This code must be done one time when HighlightReconciler is created.

 * when you select a symbol and the server is not ready you have a timeout and higlight is not done.

IMHO I think the HighlightsFinder job should not exists: instead of using job you should use thenAccept like this:

--------------------------------------------------
request = info.getLanguageClient().getTextDocumentService().documentHighlight(params)
request.thenAccept(result -> {updateAnnotations(result)})
--------------------------------------------------

With this code you avoid using a job and you fix problem when highlight is done when server is ready.

If you wish I could do a PR.

